С выхода новой Зельды - The Legend of Zelda: Link’s Awakening - прошло уже чуть больше недели. За это время я наиграл в неё столько, сколько мне позволяла работа (т.е. очень немного), но достаточно, чтобы поделиться своим мнением об игре и рассказать вообще, что она из себя представляет!
⠀
Главное, что нужно понять и уяснить - эта и предыдущая (Breath of the Wild) АБСОЛЮТНО разные игры. Не нужно ждать от этой продолжение предыдущей, чтобы не разочароваться🔴
⠀
Зачем вышла эта игра? Дело в том, что Nintendo решила обновить классику со своей первой портативной консоли, серьезно подтянув ей внешний вид, но практически ничего не меняя по части геймплея.
⠀
В далеком 1993 году The Legend of Zelda: Link’s Awakening стала не только первой игрой серии для дебютной портативной консоли Nintendo, но и была новатором в парочке других областей. Проект, в частности, предложил схему управления, где предметы из инвентаря можно «цеплять» сразу на две клавиши, а заодно подарил Линку возможность прыгать, чего в «Зельде» с видом сверху еще не встречалось.
Спустя пять лет, уже на Game Boy Color, вышла обновленная версия, где добавилось небольшое, но красочное подземелье, а монохром сменился цветной картинкой. Сейчас же Link’s Awakening добралась до Switch с кардинально переработанной графикой, однако практически во всем остальном она осталась верна первоисточнику из начала девяностых.
⠀
Игра для меня оказалась очень сложной, за чуть больше недели я собрал 2/8 нужных предметов, игра постоянно вызывает у меня чувство агрессии😆 Но при этом я с огромным удовольствием блуждаю по острову в поисках ответов! Я принципиально не смотрю видеопрохождение (хоть и понимаю, что сдамся в будущем, если буду так тупить) - хочу сам решить все загадки!
⠀
Link’s Awakening больше похожа на музейный экспонат. Его достали из кладовки, сдули пыль, немного отреставрировали и вновь представили публике. На него интересно посмотреть, чтобы понять, как игры работали раньше. Знакомым с оригиналом наверняка захочется узнать, как он преобразился в новой версии. Возможно, для кого-то это будет первая The Legend of Zelda.
⠀

Los Farfetch'd que habitan en Galar pueden evolucionar a Sirfetch'd tras participar en numerosos combates. Son calmados y serenos y, a la hora de luchar, para ellos lo primero es jugar limpio. Tal es la nobleza que demuestran en combate que a menudo aparecen como tema central en muchas obras de arte. Un cuadro en concreto, muy famoso en la región de Galar, representa la escena de un duelo entre un Sirfetch'd y un Escavalier.

The Farfetch’d of the Galar region can evolve into Sirfetch'd after experiencing many battles. They are calm and collected, and they make a point of always battling fairly. They are so noble in battle that they are often chosen as a motif for paintings. Of particular note is a painting—famous in the Galar region—that depicts a duel between a Sirfetch'd and an Escavalier.

caption.text:
I'm finally getting hyped for Sword & Shield!

I have adored what they have shown in the most recent trailers! Pokémon Camp looks like a ton of fun, the Curry mini-game reminds me of the Poffin mini-game in DPP, the towns look vibrant & full of life, customization options are tight and the Pokémon have all been fantastic so far! Not to mention, the way they're treating online battles and the new moves being introduced look like it's going to change the competitive scene for the better! I will always be an advocate for anything that improves the competitive gameplay!

However, I'm still disappointed that I haven't been blown away by anything for the first set of Pokémon games on a Nintendo Home Console. I honestly believe that Game Freak isn't taking enough time to make these games as great as they should be. I am NOT a defender of the "they have the Anime & TCG releases to worry about" because that just gives more excuses for not making the game we all know they are capable of creating. For a while, the fanbase on both sides of the argument took a toll on my passion for Pokémon. I even went through a phase where I questioned whether or not I wanted to buy these games at all.

These feelings have since passed. A lot of my criticisms, though still deep within my mind, are nothing but conjecture at this point. I need to get my hands on the games and find out if my disappointment is warranted or not. Hopefully, I am wrong and these games turn out fantastic! 😁

I hope you all know that it isn't my intention to spread any negativity towards these games! If I don't agree with something, especially if it's a thing I'm passionate about, I'm not just going to remain silent because it annoys people or hurts their feelings. I hope you all undestand!

Criticism ≠ Hate

caption.text:
Dragon's Lair Trilogy by @limitedrungames (Nintendo Switch Limited Run 36, 2019)

Dragon's Lair Trilogy includes are all three arcade classics! Dragon's Lair, Space Ace and Dragon's Lair 2: Time Warp.

In Dragon's Lair, you play the heroic Dirk the Daring, a valiant knight on a quest to rescue the fair princess from the clutches of an evil dragon!

Space Ace will have you take control of Ace - Defender of justice, truth, and the planet Earth! Ace is being attacked by the evil Commander Borf. Struggle with Dexter to regain his manhood. Destroy the Infanto-Ray. Defeat the evil Borf! Be valiant space warrior, the fate of Earth is in your hands!

Dragon’s Lair II: Time Warp once again has you leading Dirk on a perilous quest! Spirited away to a wrinkle in time by the evil wizard Mordroc, Princess Daphne will be forced to marry the wicked Mordroc unless Dirk can save her. Once the casket of doom has opened, Mordroc will place the death ring upon Daphne’s finger in marriage, and she will be lost forever in the Time Warp.

Forget hours let's talk days because I'm sure I've spent mutiple weeks playing that game none stop after work!!! The reason why I love it so much is one because of all the expansions, its like a wonderland that you can get lost in and forget about all the stressful things going on in your life! Another game that I would say is an honorable mention for me is ratchet and clank omggggggg I love that game I beat that game in 3 days because I couldn't get enough that whole space theme adventure game had me hooked I hope they make more in the future!!!⁣

'S post//
Finally guy's Pokemon gen 8 anime news out now 😍 .....! New trailer..... ↑↑ //•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
According to the trailer, Ash is still on his quest to become a Pokemon Master after winning his first-ever league. He will meet a boy named Gou who has Scorbunny as his partner, but this new protagonist won't be a sidekick. The show makes it clear Gou will be on equal footing with Ash as the boy tries to catch every kind of Pokemon including Mew. His desire to find all of these creatures will lead Gou around the world, so fans are eager to see how Ash's story intertwines with the newcomer.

Looking at the trailer, you can see the animation style of Pokemon: The Series will be a bit different from the last anime. Pokemon the Series: Sun and Moon took a drastically different approach to animation with its loose aesthetic. Now, this upcoming series will continue that overall look, but Pokemon has tightened up pieces of its design to reflect the anime's original seasons from years ago. The upcoming series looks like a true hybrid of Pokemon's past animation, so fans are eager to see the show drop on November 17.

So, what do you think about this new Pokemon anime's aesthetic so far? Let me know in the comments ......... !!!! ''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''

preview_comments.text: Am still playing link's Awakening and I can tell you this those of you say that it's too cartoon with cartoon graphics wish the graphics to be realistic something is wrong with you.All of us that grow up with Nintendo understand that Nintendo had better games but on top of that those games are fun and beautiful.This game was so fun I've made it my mission to beat it in %100 cleared,again I have never or even played link's away before in my life,when I heard about this I was like hmm I need to check this game out but never know the original came from the game boy but not only that it was a stand alone game that did not have Zelda and the final boss of the game.I've did some digging and I have leaned that this game had a lot of features that did not made in into the Zelda game on snes and it was a side project for developers that want to see what the game boy can do and realized it can do much more.This game is beautiful and great for those who never heard or even played link's Awakening,am very happy that Nintendo is still doing great things with their huge titles and keep it the same but with some updates and never try to change from the original like some other video game companys try to change from the original but end up making the game not good like road rush from EA where they failed and should keep it the same with HD graphics.Nintendo will always be in our hearts because of the memorys that we had as kids growing up and now that we are getting older the developers are getting to so the pe that are giving us great games that they worked so hard day and night thank you for are childhood and keep on giving your all to make wonderful games for all ages.

caption.text: 2 years ago I was introduced to a game that changed my life. Cuphead is my favorite game of all time. The gameplay, creativity and of course the animation made me fall in love instantly. I still play it all the time and I’m still as amazed by it as I was the first time I played it. Cuphead is the reason I’m an artist and the reason I am currently in school for 2D animation. My dream is to work for Studio MDHR someday. Cuphead has had an huge impact on my life and I can’t thank Studio MDHR enough for that. This birthday card that I made is the least I could do to show my appreciation. Happy Birthday Cuphead! A brilliantly realized, brutal, unforgiving and bloody Metroidvania that is the next best thing to any Dark Souls successors made previously as a sidescroller. Shoutout to any SoulsBorne players out there this game is a must play with lore containing immense depth, secrets & revisiting places will reward you in ways that will blow your brains out. Interactions with the NPC's, Boss Battles n Puzzles that just took everything in me to solve out..too much to absorb in a single playthrough all your questions n exploration wont end like a good ol souls game. As my 2 playthroughs come to an end i await a DLC to this amazing piece of art. 🖤 #blasphemous #indiegame #indiegames #kicksrarter #gaming #gaming #gaminglife #gamerguy #gamer #gamereview #ps4 #xbox #pc #nintendoswitch #metroidvania #sidescrolling #darksouls #bloodborne #soulsborne #deathsgambit #darkness #penitent #horror #nidz

caption.text:
Song of the Day (requested by @ultimate_anhydrous): That’s right, from now on I will cover remixes of song from other games (like Smash bros remixes) today’s song is Battle! Team Galactic! Originally from Pokemon Diamond, Pearl and Platinum, the theme was remixed in Super Smash Bros Brawl and kept all the way through Ultimate.
My thoughts: I LOVE THIS THEME! For me it brings so many childhood memories of Team Galactic and Subspace, I still remember when I had trouble trying to find the song and when I played Platinum and heard it I was screaming. This song has a very special place in my heart. •Follow for more Nintendo
